SUMMARY:April Free First Sunday
DESCRIPTION:Join the Japanese American Museum of Oregon for April Free First Sunday! \n\n\n\nApril sponsored in memory of Mary and William Sadataki. \n\n\n\nAdmission is free all day\, 11am-4pm\, and includes access to JAMO’s current exhibition\, Minidoka on Our Minds. \n\n\n\nIt’s National “Go For Broke” Day – celebrate the 442nd Regimental Combat Team\, the most decorated unit in US military history. Come to the JAMO library for a new documentary about the Hood River Incident and a coloring activity about the 442nd.
URL:https://jamo.org/event/april-free/
LOCATION:Japanese American Museum of Oregon\, 411 NW Flanders Street (Entrance on NW 4th Ave)\, Portland\, OR\, 97209
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://jamo.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/2026-April-FFS-Insta-45.jpg
END:VEVENT
