SUMMARY:Cherry Blossom Bazaar
DESCRIPTION:The Japanese American Museum of Oregon PresentsThe 2026 Cherry Blossom BazaarA Vintage Sale of Japanese Treasures \n\n\n\nThe Cherry Blossom Bazaar has something for every age\, taste\, and budget! Hunt for hidden treasure at this unique sale of Japanese collectibles\, clothing\, dishware\, furniture\, and more. \n\n\n\nSaturday & SundayApril 11-1210am – 4pm \n\n\n\nThe Povey Building408 NW 5th Ave\, 1st FloorPortland\, OR 97209 \n\n\n\nYou are also invited to join us for a Preview Night BenefitGet first pick of the merchandise!Friday\, April 10\, 5-7pmFriends of JAMO: $25General public: $50Get tickets \n\n\n\nThe regular Bazaar hours are Saturday and Sunday\, April 11-12 and entry is FREE. On April 10\, there will be a special Preview Night Benefit for those who want first pick of the merchandise\, with tickets priced at $25-50 for entry. \n\n\n\nHow to join in the fun: \n\n\n\n\nGet your tickets for the preview.\n\n\n\nDonate your Japanese items through April 7\, by appointment only. Contact us at info@jamo.org or 503-224-1458.\n\n\n\nShop ’til you drop! Choose from an eclectic array of Japanese collectibles and gifts.\n\n\n\nVolunteer and help make this fun community sale a success. Contact Jeremy or fill out a volunteer application and be sure to select “Off-site Events” as the type of volunteer work you are interested in.
URL:https://jamo.org/event/bazaar/
LOCATION:Povey Building\, 408 NW 5th Ave\, Portland\, Oregon\, 97209\, United States
CATEGORIES:For Families,Fundraiser,Shopping
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://jamo.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/2026-Cherry-Blossom-Bazaar-Poster-DIGITAL.jpg
END:VEVENT
