SUMMARY:Book Launch: The Centennial Edition of The Toledo Incident of 1925 with Author Ted Cox
DESCRIPTION:Join author Ted Cox for a presentation of his newly revised centennial edition of The Toledo Incident of 1925: Three Days That Made History in Toledo\, Oregon. Book signing to follow – books will be available for purchase at the event. \n\n\n\nSaturday April 18\, 2026 @ 1PM220 NW 2nd AvenuePortland\, Oregon 97209 \n\n\n\nAbout the Book: \n\n\n\nIn July 1925\, the Pacific Spruce Company brought Japanese laborers to Toledo to work the green chain\, a particularly dangerous step in the lumber mill process. Only two days after their arrival\, town residents formed a mob and violently expelled them. The Toledo Incident is the definitive book detailing this incident\, what led to it\, and the lawsuit brought – and won – by the Japanese workers. \n\n\n\nThe centennial edition of contains new material and previously unpublished images. More importantly\, it documents a district federal court jury verdict in 1926 that affirmed that lawful resident aliens\, including immigrants ineligible for US citizenship\, possessed enforceable protections and that those rights could be upheld through monetary judgments. \n\n\n\nThe story has strong and timely historical relevance\, speaking to ongoing conversations about race\, justice\, immigration\, and mob violence. Commemorating the 100th anniversary of both the expulsion and the lawsuit\, this revised Centennial Edition presents a thoroughly updated account. It also clarifies the broader national context: anti-immigrant politics\, Ku Klux Klan influence\, and Oregon’s own complicated racial climate. \n\n\n\nAbout the Author:  \n\n\n\nTed W. Cox\, educator\, traveler\, and storyteller\, was born in Eugene\, Oregon\, in 1947. He earned his master’s degree in education from Oregon State University in 1975. Ted’s adventures have taken him from teaching in Sierra Leone to coaching track and field in Belize\, and later to running the beloved Old World Deli in Corvallis\, Oregon\, for more than forty years. Married to Veronica\, with two children and four grandchildren\, Ted draws on a lifetime of global experience and deep local roots to bring history vividly to life.
URL:https://jamo.org/event/toledo-incident/
LOCATION:220 PDX\, 220 NW 2nd Ave\, Portland\, Oregon\, 97209\, United States
CATEGORIES:Books and Literature
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/png:https://jamo.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Toledo-Incident-Book-Cover-smaller.png
END:VEVENT
